HEADWORD: Kingston valve
<hw>King"ston valve</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Marine Steam
Engin.)</fld> <def>A conical valve, opening outward, to close the mouth
of a pipe which passes through the side of a vessel below the water
line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kingtruss</ent>⟦br⟧
